title: For Sale:  Swenson Colt 45
location: Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: I'm an officer in the military.  I purchased this pistol during an estate sale in Washington DC around 2009.  She has been sitting in my safe since then.  I've had several people tell me it's an Armand Swenson from Paul Broom, California custom pistol.  I don't have any collectors documentation.  But I would be glad to take any pictures you would like.  Will only transfer the pistol in person or through your local gun dealer to take care of the transfer paperwork.  This is a very  tight action pistol.  No  loose  Parts.   Colt MK IV Series 80.  Government Model. FG84467This is a great looking pistol built by one of the best Colt 1911 gunsmiths around. The nickel frame really stands out on this so be sure to check our pictures. If you are a serious Colt collector, adding an Armand Swenson custom built Colt will certainly help to fill-out your collection.As written by Jason Burton at http://www.coolgunsite.com/comm_pistols/custom/swenson/swenson.htm: “Anyone who has read enough gun periodicals or has been around custom 1911s at any length has undoubtedly seen countless references to Armand Swenson and with good reason. As many have mentioned before, Swenson was one of the greatest and probably most important 1911 ‘smiths since Browning himself. Not necessarily because Swenson’s work was cosmetically perfect or without fault but because he was, to a greater or lesser extent, the first to really bring out the custom 1911 in the fashion that we know it today… or at least the first person to be widely recognized as such. While parts, techniques, technology, and the overall build of the custom 1911 have no doubt been elevated to a standard much higher than anything Swenson did the heart and soul of the custom 1911 is still firmly rooted and can be traced back to Armand Swenson’s work. Swenson paved the way for the “bulls-eye accurate and combat reliable” 1911s we have come to know and every custom maker working today owes him for that…. at least a little.”..

title: For Sale:  Very Sad
postcontent: Let me start off by saying i love this website and what it has to offer the 2A community; however, it is very disheartening to listen to my son, who is 19 and in college, say that this site has discouraged him about guns.  He has been trying to buy an affordable pistol from a private seller for his appartment, but everytime he sees one he likes the seller listed that the buyer must be 21 years of age and has to have a CWP.  It is a sad state of affairs that we have a community full of ignorant gun owners that dont realize they are creating restricitons on buying pistols through private sales.  You only have to be 18 to buy a pistol through private sale, 21 if you buy it from an FFL; being said, for those requiring a buyer to have a CWP you must be a liberal snowflake adding on unneeded restrictions.  In other words, you all are killing the newbies comming to our community with these excess restrictions.  Hopefully this post will help educate those that are ignorant.Happy Tuesday.
